        "node": {
          "id": 106071,
          "name": {
            "first": "Kentarou",
            "last": "Haneda",
            "native": "羽田健太郎"
          },
          "language": "JAPANESE",
          "image": {
            "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/staff/large/n106071-OgxWeVo50cVY.png",
            "medium": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/staff/medium/n106071-OgxWeVo50cVY.png"
          },
          "description": "[Wiki (jp)](https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E7%BE%BD%E7%94%B0%E5%81%A5%E5%A4%AA%E9%83%8E) | [Wiki (en)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kentar%C5%8D_Haneda)\n\nKentarou Haneda was a Japanese pianist, composer and arranger of popular anime and movies and video game music.\n\nAfter graduating from the Toho Gakuen School of Music, he taught as a professor at the Tokyo College of Music. He was best known as composer of Wizardry music which was ported to NES and SNES console by Ascii at early 1990, The [Super Dimension Fortress Macross](https://anilist.co/anime/1088/) series, [Barefoot Gen](https://anilist.co/anime/1824/), Ys Symphony, Symphony Sorcerian and Genso Suikoden Ongaku-shu.\n\nHaneda passed away from liver cancer on June 2, 2007.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)",
